%h1 FruitBack

- if user_signed_in?
  %p
    = "You are signed in as #{current_user.name}. Please take a look on the navigationbar..."
    
- else
  %div.well
    %h2 
      Sign in
      = simple_form_for(resource, :as => resource_name, :url => session_path(resource_name), :html => { :class => 'form-horizontal' }) do |f|
        
        .form-inputs
          = f.input :email, :required => false, :autofocus => true
          = f.input :password, :required => false
          = f.input :remember_me, :as => :boolean if devise_mapping.rememberable?
          = f.button :submit, "Sign in", class: 'btn btn-success'
    
    %p
      Don't have an customer account? 
      = link_to 'Sign up', new_user_registration_path

- content_for :sidebar do
  %h2 What is fruitback?
  %p
    Fruitback is an open source project started in February 2013 at the University of Bremen.
  
  %h3 For your web app
  %p
    Embed Fruitback in your web app with just a single snippet of code to create a seamless customer service experience for users.
  
  %h3 For your brand
  %p
    Fruitback lets your users post, discuss, and search for ideas. 